an age is most accurate in the older age ranges. Correspondence between microscopically and macroscopically determined ages does not necessarily confirm the accuracy of either. It is also suggested that a combination of histological ageing and pubic symphysis ageing has the potential of producing more accurate results than either by itself. © 1993 Academic Press Limited.},
